Package org.e2immu.support

package org.e2immu.support
  • Class Summary
    Class
    Description
    AddOnceSet<V>
    Example of a freezable set, which disallows both removal and attempts to write an object a second time.
    Either<A,​B>
    An class holding either an object of type A, or one of type B; it cannot hold both, nor can it hold neither.
    EventuallyFinal<T>
    Eventually level 2 immutable class, which holds arbitrary values for one field until a final value is written.
    FirstThen<S,​T>
    An object which first holds an object of type S, and, in the second and final stage of its life-cycle, holds an object of type T.
    FlipSwitch
    Most simple example of an eventually level 2 immutable type: the object's state marker is the content of the object.
    Freezable
    Super-class for eventually immutable types.
    Lazy<T>
    Implementation of a lazy value, where null is used to indicate that the value has not been evaluated yet.
    SetOnce<T>
    Simple example eventually level 2 immutable type which can hold a single value.
    SetOnceMap<K,​V>
    Example of an eventually level 2 immutable map, where each key can be put only once, and removal is not permitted.
